The paper deals with the performance of machine learning algorithms and the role of training data in their performance. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational engineering (cs.CE), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). However, given the focus on machine learning performance and accountability, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
